  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoring Hope to Vulnerable Communities Affected by Cyclone Chalane and Eloise</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1 Increased access to clean and safe water and sanitation for 11 500 households in disaster affected districts (Bikita Buhera and Chipinge)
2. Improved knowledge  and response  to Covid19 prevention practices 
3. Improved household nutrition and incomes through sustainable agricultural  practices and internal savings and lendings
4.Improved access to community based pyscho social support and GBV awareness information and services 
5. Enhanced greater accountability ,protection and safeguarding for disaster  affected people in Buhera, Bikita and Chipinge districts.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.The project aims to increase access to clean and safe water and sanitation for 11 500 households in disaster affected districts (Bikita Buhera and Chipinge)
2.The project aims to ensure that target communities have improved their knowledge  and response  to Covid19 prevention practices 
3.The project will aim to ensure that target communities have improved household nutrition and incomes through sustainable agricultural  practices and internal savings and lendings
4.The project will aim to ensure that target communities have improved access to community based pyscho social support and GBV awareness information and services 
5. The project will aim to ensure there is greater accountability ,protection and safeguarding for disaster  affected people in Buhera, Bikita and Chipinge districts.</narrative>
  </description>
